Well at 64+, its all about Command of Druzzil.  Now two things to be careful of:<br>
<br>
1 - They should have removed the resist adjustment for CoD in this latest patch.<br>
<br>
2 - They have modified the xp associated with Charm soloing, it was really good so we shall see how it looks now.<br>
<br>
Best places to go are all in PoP.  Why?  Simple CRs.  Charming is a high risk/high reward strategy.  I am not big on CRs deep in Sebillis, when I can get better xp in PoN.  Tier 2 zones are even better, but again high risk.  Now luckily for me, my alt cleric got CoD flagged at level 54 so I can rezz myself in a Tier 2 zone.<br>
<br>
As for tactics, there are basically 2 schools but they have a couple of things in common:<br>
<br>
1 - Always have the charmed mob tashed<br>
2 - Root the mob under attack (so in case charm breaks you only have one mob hitting you)<br>
3 - Don't be afraid to run like a little girl if things go wrong<br>
<br>
Now the 2 schools I have seen are:<br>
<br>
- Keep your pet alive (Dire Charmed pets basically are always here).  Slow the mobs under attack.  DoT them as well.  If your pet is DCed, buff it.  Use Bedlam/Uproar as a &quot;rune&quot;.<br>
<br>
- Let your pet die.  Maximize your pets damage with haste and kill it off after the first kill.  Very high risk as even green pets in the planes hit fast and relatively hard.<br>
<br>
Best loot for stuff like this is the PoJ basement, although the xp will pretty much suck.  If you don't care about xp, at 64 you should be able to Dire Charm a froglock in Sebillis.  Get a shaman if possible as they will heal themselves and you.<br>
<br>
As for soloing Dragons, maybe in WW.  I can't think of anything in WL that can come close to taking Woushi.  I would think a Velium Hound would make a nice pet (If they are charmable, I have never tried).<br>
<br>
Last thing, there are some clicky snare items in the game.  1 from the Warrens/Stonebrunt.  The other is from Fungus Grove.  Having a snared pet is very handy as they are easier to run away from.<br>
<br>
